Five people left injured after a collision last night. The Netcare 911 spokesman, Shawn Herbst said Netcare 911 responded to reports of a collision on the corners of Robert Broom Drive and Paardekraal Drive in Krugersdorp. He said reports from the scene indicate that an SUV and two cars were involved in a collision. "Medics assessed the scene and found that five people had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate with one person sustaining serious injuries," said Herbst. He further stated that the seriously injured patient was treated on scene by an advanced life support paramedic and once stabilised all the patients were transported by ambulance to a hospital for further treatment.